Now, we'll design the CSS styles to mimic the image you've provided.

**styles/globals.css**:

```css
body {
    margin: 0;
    font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
    background-image: url('/background-image.jpg');
    background-size: cover;
    background-position: center;
    height: 100vh;
    overflow: hidden;
}

.container {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    height: 100vh;
    justify-content: space-between;
}

.header {
    display: flex;
    justify-content: space-between;
    align-items: center;
    padding: 10px 20px;
}

.logo {
    font-size: 22px;
    font-weight: bold;
}

.controls {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
}

.search-box {
    margin-top: 20vh;
    text-align: center;
}

.search-input {
    width: 60%;
    padding: 10px;
    font-size: 16px;
    border: 1px solid #ccc;
    border-radius: 3px;
}

.modal {
    position: absolute;
    top: 20%;
    left: 25%;
    width: 50%;
    background-color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.9);
    padding: 20px;
    border-radius: 10px;
    box-shadow: 0 0 15px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.2);
}

.modal h1 {
    font-size: 24px;
    margin-bottom: 15px;
}

.modal p {
    font-size: 18px;
}
```

Next, we'll create our webpage component:

**pages/index.js**:

```javascript
import Head from 'next/head'

export default function Home() {
  return (
    <div className="container">
      <Head>
        <title>Bing Webpage Clone</title>
        <link rel="icon" href="/favicon.ico" />
      </Head>

      <header className="header">
        <span className="logo">Microsoft Bing</span>
        <div className="controls">
          {/* Add icons and other controls as needed */}
        </div>
      </header>

      <div className="search-box">
        <input className="search-input" type="text" placeholder="Search the web" />
      </div>

      <div className="modal">
        <h1>Introducing the new Bing</h1>
        <p>Ask real questions. Get complete answers.</p>
        <button>Learn more</button>
      </div>

      {/* You can add the footer and other elements here */}
    </div>
  )
}
```

Make sure you add a background image (`background-image.jpg`) to the public folder, which resembles the image you've provided.

Note: This is a basic structure and may require some fine-tuning to match the exact design. You may also need to add icons and other UI elements as per your requirements. Additionally, you might want to find a similar font or use web fonts to match the exact font styles.
